      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): inherit config auth.profiles when default agent store is empty",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAfter the SQLite auth profile refactor (#89102), the default agent (`main`) loses all auth profiles and fails with \"Missing API key\" when it never had per-agent legacy JSON files (`auth-profiles.json`).\n\nSub-agents with legacy files get migrated to SQLite during `doctor` repair, but the default agent may have resolved its credentials from global `auth.profiles` in `openclaw.json` + env vars / secret refs — no per-agent JSON files to migrate, so the SQLite store remains empty.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. `resolveAuthProfileEligibility` (order.ts)\n\nFor `api_key` and `token` profiles defined in config `auth.profiles`, a missing store credential is no longer a hard failure. The actual key/token can come from env vars or secret refs later in the credential resolution chain.\n\n### 2. `loadAuthProfileStoreForAgent` (store.ts) \n\nWhen no persisted store exists and the config has `auth.profiles` entries, inherit those profile metadata into the in-memory store so the eligibility/order system sees them.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- `vitest run src/agents/auth-profiles/order.test.ts` — 36 PASS, 0 FAIL\n- TypeScript compilation: no errors\n\nFixes #93145\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
